               <p>1918. <persName id="def1-1918-18470816" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1918-18470816" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1918-18470816" type="age" value="18"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1918-18470816" type="surname" value="PRINCE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1918-18470816" type="given" value="SAMUEL CHARLES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">SAMUEL CHARLES PRINCE</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18470816-1918-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18470816-1918-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18470816-1918-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp> for stealing 1 half-eagle, value 28<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the monies of <persName id="t18470816-name-1024" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1024" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1024" type="surname" value="ORR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1024" type="given" value="ERIC"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18470816-1918-offence-1 t18470816-name-1024"></join>Eric Orr</persName>; in a vessel in a port of entry and discharge.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1025" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1025" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1025" type="surname" value="ORR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1025" type="given" value="ERIC"></interp>ERIC ORR.</persName>
                  </hi> I am second mate of the <hi rend="italic">James Edwards</hi>, which is in the St. Katharine's Docks; the prisoner was steward. On the 26th of July I lost a half-eagle, which is worth about 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 8<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—the prisoner had wanted to borrow money of me the day before, and I told him I had not got any—he had no business in my berth that I know of—I missed this piece of money—I took the prisoner to my room and spoke to him—he stated at first that he had not taken it—at last he said he had taken the half-eagle piece, and told me to say nothing about it, that he might not have discharge—I told him there was no necessity for it, he had been bad enough without—he had put the money in a house, and spent a cent of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I never took it all; I went to speak to the mate, and this witness called me into the state-room, and had a rope's-end; he said I had taken the piece; I said I had not, but sooner than have a piece of work I would pay more than the value of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1026" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1026" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1026" type="surname" value="GIFFORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1026" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT GIFFORD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) I took the prisoner—he said he knew nothing about it; but sooner than have any piece of work he would pay five times the amount—the next morning he asked if he should plead guilty—I told him I should give him no advice—he then said, "I took the money, but it was through drink and the persuasion of another party."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470816-name-1027" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1027" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1027" type="surname" value="WILSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470816-name-1027" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN WILSON.</persName>
                  </hi> I live at No.4, Neptune-court. On Sunday night the prisoner came to sleep in that house, and he left his coat for the price of the room, he had no money—on Monday night, the 26th, he came again with a gold piece.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I had twenty dollars which the captain paid me; it was my own money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">to</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">ERIC ORR.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did he received twenty dollars? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> The cap<lb></lb>tain would not give him a farthing—I swear he never had a farthing—his pay was twenty dollars a month; but he acted in such a way that he was not worth a farthing—he wasted more victuals, and spoiled more than he was worth.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> This witness told me the captain was a very bad captain, and he said he would take his gold watch and throw it overboard; I am as innocent as you are; I did not take it. I assure; I had my trunk full of clothes, and 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. owing to me; the Magistrate said I might have them, but the ship was gone to sea and I could not get them.</p>
               <p>
